  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">American Red Cross School Vouchers in Port au Prince</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected population(s), School children</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After the earthquake, many Haitians lost their primary source of income and were left without the means to meet basic needs, including sending their children to school.  The American Red Cross helped displaced families in three camps in the Croix Deprez neighborhood by directly paying second and third trimester school fees as well as providing grants for displaced families to cover education-related expenses like uniforms, transportation and lunch money. This project reached 2,727 children.</narrative>
  </description>
